CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 28, 1956, page A19, reads: "Top winners in the Metoka Club's scholarships were Maurice Johnson, first; Robert Russell, Marlene Jones, Joan Graves, Lee Bertha West and Barbara Ashby. They received their awards at the club's annual garden party last Thursday. - 'Teenie' Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of two young men and four young women, left to right: Maurice Johnson, Robert Russell, Marlene Jones, Joan Graves, Lee Bertha West, and Barbara Ashby, wearing Metoka Club "scholarship" ribbons, posed behind gazing ball outdoors, with VFW sign on brick building in background
